  "summary": "Dependency-confusion PoC with install-time and import-time beacons to webhook.site",
  "details": "Package self-identifies as a dependency-confusion proof-of-concept impersonating an internal/private package name. setup.py overrides the install command to issue an HTTP GET to https://webhook.site/\u003ctoken\u003e?status=cubifyanything_installed during `pip install`, and cubifyanything/__init__.py issues a second HTTP GET to webhook.site with `status=imported` on every `import cubifyanything`. Both beacons run automatically without user consent, exposing the installer's source IP and confirming to a third-party logging endpoint that the impersonated internal name resolved to this public package. Any organization that has an internal package named `cubifyanything` and accidentally resolves from public PyPI will execute these beacons, signaling that the internal name exists and is exploitable.",
